<br>
The Hole - I posted a semi-guide to it on another thread, but in essence you just camp the first 6 spawns. There is no way you can die here if you're only killing the first 6, which will be about all you can handle at 52. If things get out of hand, simply jump into the water and zone. The mob won't directly follow you - he'll have to go around the rock thing and then into the water.<br>
<br>
Cobalt Scar - I haven't tried here myself, but I hear it's decent exp.<br>
<br>
Dreadlands - I have done this at 52 while trying to kill the Dread Widow...it was actually semi-good exp. There are still blues and light blues, so just keep your 51 earth DS'ed and pull like crazy. Fun to do while camping the Dread Widow...grrr never even saw her <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
That's about all I can think of....check the other posts in the forum for more info. <p><b><font size="1"><a target="new" href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=60066">Balthemal </a><br>53 Mage</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezzn1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezzn1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/01 12:48:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Pure SOLO Spots at 52 :0)</span><hr size=1> is there anyway of going farther into the Hole at 54?? past the first 6? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalanzsonofanz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 508<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/01 6:06:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=145.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Tracky's Teeth!</span><hr size=1> After <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Lake Fillomen</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> went basically green, I regularly soloed from 52-54 at the various <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spectral Keeper</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> camps in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Trakanon's Teeth</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  While some are green or light blue, they spawn fairly quickly, and can be easily single pulled.  The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spectral Commanders</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Champions</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that spawn there are pure melee, and even easier.  The <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Keepers</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> are wizards, so be prepared to take some fire-based nukes for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, but nothing you can't handle, at least if you are a beefy human like myself, and not one of those pinata-type races, that collapse upon impact.<br>
<br>
There are three camps of 3-5 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spectrals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> right near the entrance to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Emerald Jungle</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  With your back to EJ, there are two sets of ruins on your left, towards <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sebilis</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and one larger ruin on your right, towards <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Field of Bone</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, all withing a short distance of the zone in.  Once you have the hang of it, you can clean out all three camps in 15-20 minutes, by which time the first camp will have respawned.<br>
<br>
Another nice thing about this place is if you can get a tracker to partner with you, you can do the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Hunter/Forager</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cycle for experience and modest loot.  Almost everything in the cycle is 45th level, and nothing is above 51st.  All is doable, either with pet as exclusive tank, buffed and healed by partner or small group, or supporting a supported melee (i.e. tank plus healer/buffer).<br>
<br>
Once you ding 55, and get <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Call of the Hero</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, you can start in on <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sebilis</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  There is also a camp of three <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Spectrals</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> just outside the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sebilis Bubble</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, so if you are interested in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Sebilis</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>before</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> 55th, you can solo these for experience, instead of just sitting on your butt <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> LFG</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Abuser of EZCodes<br>
